-- Indian shares hit lowest close in 1-1/2 weeks; lenders drag on FII sales
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 06:09AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 29 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell for a third straight session on Tuesday, continuing to retreat from record highs hit last week to mark their lowest close in 1-1/2 weeks as lenders including HDFC Bank were hit after foreign investors sold index futures.

HDFC Bank Ltd <HDBK.NS> provisionally fell 1.1 percent, while State Bank of India <SBI.NS> ended lower 2.1 percent.